        "title": "fix(mcp): dispose bundled runtimes after one-shot runs",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Replaces the broad source PR #68450 with a narrow MCP runtime cleanup patch.\n- Ensures isolated cron, heartbeat, and follow-up one-shot runs retire bundled MCP runtimes at the outer run boundary, including rotated session IDs.\n- Keeps cleanup failures isolated so reply completion and typing teardown still run.\n\n## Credit\nThis carries forward the useful cleanup direction from @seanniu93 in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/68450 with attribution preserved.\n\n## Review Notes\n- Do not include unrelated Matrix extension edits.\n- Address the Codex finding about rotated cron session IDs.\n- Address the Greptile finding that cleanup errors must not prevent replyOperation.complete() or typing teardown.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm check:changed\n\nProjectClownfish replacement details:\n- Cluster: ghcrawl-156747-autonomous-smoke\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/68450\n- Credit: Credit @seanniu93 for the source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/68450 and the isolated one-shot cleanup approach.; Do not carry unrelated Matrix extension changes from #68450.; Address hydrated review-bot findings: dispose all rotated cron session IDs, ensure cleanup failures cannot skip replyOperation.complete()/typing teardown, and document or avoid the connectInFlight/sessions ordering hazard.\n- Validation: pnpm check:changed\n",
